  "text": "However, the mechanisms that regulate the synthesis and pathogenicity of HIT antibodies have not been fully defined and are possibly influenced by genetic factors. In this study, we investigated the potential impact of 3 SNPs (Q276P, R326Q and D872E) affecting CD148 on the synthesis of antibodies to PF4/H and the occurrence of HIT. Our results demonstrated that patients carrying the CD148 276P and 326Q alleles appeared less at risk of HIT although they had developed significant levels of antibodies to H/PF4 (OR = 0.47; 95% CI 0.25-0.89 and OR = 0.50 95% CI 0.27-0.92, respectively). In accordance with previous studies, we found a strong linkage disequilibrium between both CD148 Q276P and R326Q polymorphisms [CITATION_1] .",
